Title   : Trump-Xi summit in South Korea on track amid trade tensions 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-10-14T04:59:32
Fetched : 2025-10-14T09:28:37.525271
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/trump-xi-summit-in-south-korea-on-track-amid-trade-tensions/slideshow/124544033.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
US President Donald Trump is on track to meet Chinese leader Xi Jinping in South Korea in late October. The meeting, planned during the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) summit, aims to ease tensions between the two countries over tariffs and export controls. (Source: Reuters)
Agencies
2/7
Trade Tensions Spike
Trade tensions flared after China announced tightened export controls on rare earths. Trump responded with a threat of new tariffs, triggering a sharp market reaction and raising concerns over the state of US-China economic relations.
TIL Creatives
3/7
Communications Ongoing
Despite recent tensions, substantial communication continues between the US and China. US Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent confirmed that dialogue has de-escalated the situation. Staff-level talks are expected this week in Washington alongside IMF and World Bank meetings.
IANS
4/7
Stock Market Reaction
Markets reacted positively to signs of progress. Asian stocks made a tentative rebound, while Wall Street ended up to 2.2% higher. Investor worries about a stock market boom driven by artificial intelligence and its potential impact on employment eased slightly.
Agencies
5/7
US Pushback on China
The United States responded firmly to China’s rare earth controls. Bessent described China’s actions as provocative but emphasised continued communication with allies, including Europe, India, and other Asian democracies. China, in turn, blamed the US for rising tensions and defended its export curbs.
Agencies
6/7
Rare Earth Licensing Changes
China’s new regulations require foreign companies to obtain Chinese export licences if their final products involve Chinese materials or equipment. The US has rejected these licensing requirements, highlighting the growing complexity in the global supply chain for rare earths.
Agencies
7/7
Outlook
The threat of immediate tariffs has been delayed, with Trump announcing that new tariffs will not take effect until 1 November. Bessent expressed optimism, stating that the US-China relationship remains positive and that open lines of communication have been restored. (Disclaimer: This slideshow has been sourced from Reuters)

Title   : Interise Trust to raise more than ₹2,000 crore via bonds, bankers say
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-10-14T04:47:02
Fetched : 2025-10-14T09:28:37.525407
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/interise-trust-to-raise-more-than-2000-crore-via-bonds-bankers-say/article70161234.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
India's Interise Trust plans to raise up to ₹2,075 crore ($233.9 million) through two series of bonds maturing in 19 years, five months and 15 days each, three bankers said on Tuesday. The Infrastructure Investment Trust will pay a coupon of 6.96% and 7.3014%, respectively, payable quarterly, they said.
"Staggered Redemption for both series will start from December 31, 2025, quarterly thereafter and on maturity as per redemption schedule," one of the bankers said. One issue has a call option at end of three years and another at end of 10 years, they added. The trust has invited commitment bids for the issue on Wednesday, they said.
The company did not immediately respond to a Reuters email seeking comment.
Here is the list of deals reported so far on October 14:
Issuer Tenure Coupon (in %) Issue size (in Bidding bln rupees)* date Rating
Interise 19 years, 5 6.96 10.5 October 15 AAA Trust months and (India 15 days Rating, Icra)
Interise 19 years, 5 7.3014 10.25 October 15 AAA Trust months and (India 15 days Rating, Icra)
1 year and 5 7.55 25 October 14 AAA Poonawalla months (Crisil Fincorp )
Poonawalla 1 year and 9 7.5285 5 October 14 AAA Fincorp months (Crisil 2027)
Reissue * Size includes base plus greenshoe for some issues
Published on October 14, 2025

Title   : Trump hails India as ‘great country’; predicts India-Pakistan will ‘live very nicely together’
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-10-14T01:24:26
Fetched : 2025-10-14T09:28:37.525513
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/world/trump-hails-india-as-great-country-predicts-india-pakistan-will-live-very-nicely-together/article70161113.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
US President Donald Trump on Monday praised India and Prime Minister Narendra Modi without naming him, saying “India is a great country with a good friend of mine at the top”.
Trump, addressing a summit of world leaders at this Egyptian city after a ceasefire reached in Gaza ending the Israel-Hamas war, said from the podium that he thinks “India and Pakistan will live very nicely together”.
“India is a great country with a very good friend of mine at the top and he’s just done a fantastic job. I think Pakistan and India are going to live very nicely together,” Trump said while looking at Pakistan Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif who was standing behind him, as he responded with a chuckle.
Sharif credits Trump, pushes Nobel nomination
Earlier praising Sharif and his “favourite field marshal” Pakistan army chief Gen Asim Munir, Trump also invited the Pakistan prime minister to address the gathering.
Sharif said peace has been achieved in the Middle East after “untiring and relentless efforts” of President Trump.
“Pakistan had nominated President Trump for the Nobel Peace Prize for his outstanding (and) extraordinary contributions to first stop the war between India and Pakistan and then achieve a ceasefire along with his very wonderful team,” he said.
Sharif said he would like to nominate Trump again for the Nobel Peace Prize for “saving millions of lives not only in South Asia but also in the Middle East”.
After missing out on the Nobel Peace Prize, Trump has claimed to have resolved eight wars, including the one between India and Pakistan, saying, he did not do this for the Nobel.
Trump has been claiming to resolve seven conflicts till now, including the one between India and Pakistan. However, he has now increased that figure to eight after adding the Israel-Gaza conflict.
Since May 10, when Trump announced on social media that India and Pakistan had agreed to a “full and immediate” ceasefire after a “long night” of talks mediated by Washington, he has repeated his claim dozens of times that he “helped settle” the conflict between India and Pakistan.
India has consistently maintained that the understanding on cessation of hostilities with Pakistan was reached following direct talks between the Directors General of Military Operations (DGMOs) of the two militaries.
India launched Operation Sindoor on May 7, targeting terror infrastructure in Pakistan and Pakistan-occupied Kashmir in retaliation for the April 22 Pahalgam attack that killed 26 civilians.
India and Pakistan reached an understanding on May 10 to end the conflict after four days of intense cross-border drone and missile strikes.
Published on October 14, 2025

Title   : Interise Trust to raise over Rs 20 billion via bonds: Bankers 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-10-14T05:27:18
Fetched : 2025-10-14T09:28:37.525587
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/bonds/interise-trust-to-raise-over-rs-20-billion-via-bonds-bankers/articleshow/124544421.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Infrastructure Investment Trust will pay a coupon of 6.96% and 7.3014%, respectively, payable quarterly, they said. "Staggered Redemption for both series will start from December 31, 2025, quarterly thereafter and on maturity as per redemption schedule," one of the bankers said.
One issue has a call option at end of three years and another at end of 10 years, they added. The trust has invited commitment bids for the issue on Wednesday, they said.
Interise Trust is set to raise 20.75 billion rupees via two bond series. These bonds will mature in 19 years, five months, and 15 days. Coupons will be 6.96% and 7.3014%, paid quarterly. Staggered redemption begins December 31, 2025. One issue has a three-year call option, the other a ten-year call option. Commitment bids are invited for Wednesday.
The company did not immediately respond to a Reuters email seeking comment.
Here is the list of deals reported so far on October 14:
Issuer Tenure Coupon (in %) Issue size (in Bidding bln rupees)* date Rating Interise 19 years, 5 6.96 10.5 October 15 AAA Trust months and (India 15 days Rating, Icra) Interise 19 years, 5 7.3014 10.25 October 15 AAA Trust months and (India 15 days Rating, Icra) 1 year and 5 7.55 25 October 14 AAA Poonawalla months (Crisil Fincorp ) Poonawalla 1 year and 9 7.5285 5 October 14 AAA Fincorp months (Crisil 2027 ) Reissue * Size includes base plus greenshoe for some issues ($1 = 88.7000 Indian rupees).
