HCL Tech Q2 Live: Brokerage recommendations
Jefferies on HCL Tech
Buy, TP Rs 1730
Q2 beat estimates, with higher revenue growth & strong deal wins
HCLT raised FY26 services growth guidance to 4-5% – highest among India’s Top 5 IT firms.
HCLT’s infrastructure services lineage and AI strategy position it well to gain market share.
Raise EPS est. by 1% & expect 9% EPS CAGR in FY26-28.
Superior growth/FCF conversion will support premium valuations
Nomura on HCL Tech
Buy, TP Rs 1660
2QFY26 results – strong performance on all counts
Strong margin performance; we see normalisation of margins in FY27F
FY26E revenue guidance for services raised at lower end to 4-5% from 3-5% earlier
Focussing on AI through services route; intends to remain asset light
CITI On HCL Tech
Neutral, TP Rs 1600
Reported a good 2Q – revenues ahead & raised lower end of services revenue guidance
Fwd. looking indicators
(a) Overall revenue guidance unchanged at 3-5% yoy cc; services now at 4-5% (earlier 3-5%);
(b) Headcount +3.7% yoy
(c) LTM TCV +13% yoy;
(d) Mgmt. commentary – external environment unpredictable; business indicators promising
Raise FY27E-FY28E EPS est. by 0-1%
CLSA on HCL Tech
O-P, TP Rs 1660
Strong 2Q beat across revenue growth, Ebit margin and order booking.
It revised upwards its services business revenue growth guidance to 4-5% (from 3-5%) on back of 2Q beat and good visibility for 2H on back of strong deal wins.
For overall revenue growth though, it kept the 3-5% FY26 guidance band intact due to weakness in the software business
Believe key to HCL’s re-rating from current levels depends on Ebit margin recovering back to 18-19% in FY27
GS on HCL Tech
Maintains Neutral with a target price of ₹1,620 (vs 1,530 earlier)
Q2FY26 growth outpaced peers, with 2.4% QoQ CC revenue rise and headcount addition showing improving demand
Share gains in key renewals suggest company-specific strength rather than broad industry momentum
Some deal declines tied to Al productivity gains setu may weigh on sector valuations
FY26 services growth guidance raised to 4-5%, with expectations near ~5.1%
Nuvama on HCL Tech
Recommendation Hold; Target Price ₹1,650, Earlier Target ₹1,630
Valuations are on a par with TCS and Infosys, we see limited upside potential
Sequential broad-based growth with improved margins
Strong client interest with Al force now deployed in 47 accounts (versus 35 QoQ)
USB on Autos
While street thinks that GST cuts will lead to a medium-term entry-level and 2W demand revival, our analysis, past precedent & channel checks show consumers want to trade up to premium.
Meanwhile, upcoming regulatory changes (CAFE, 2W ABS) & state government tax hikes may erode the GST cut benefits
Prefer premiumization plays M&M, TVS & Hyundai (all Buy), while see downside risk for Hero, Bajaj (both Sell) & Maruti (Neutral)
CLSA on Autos
GST boost well-timed amid weak Q1 demand.
Consumers shifting to premium models per channel checks.
CAFE norms & ABS may dilute GST benefit.
CLSA prefers M&M, TVS, Hyundai as premiumisation plays.
Ambit on LG Electronics
Initiates coverage with Buy & TP of ₹1,820.
Exports to gain from Sri City plant expansion.
Localisation + premiumisation to lift margins.
GST cuts may aid growth revival.
Motilal Oswal on LG Electronics
Initiate with BUY rating with TP ₹1800/sh
Expected to trade at higher multiples
Strong RoE/RoIC of ~30%/66% by FY28E
High OCF conversion ~74% (FY26-28E)
Strategic localization to expand gross margins
Focus on high-margin B2B & AMC business
Leadership across key product categories
Nomura on Tata Motors
NEUTRAL | TP ₹732
PV business ₹365/share, CV ₹367/share
Premiumisation trend: surge in micro & compact SUV bookings
Management targets double-digit margins in medium term
JLR 5–7% EBIT margins may have downside risk
CV EBIT guidance 5.4–7.5% (FY24–28)
Nuvama on Just Dial
Buy, TP cut to Rs 1200
reported a weak set of Q2 with revenue at INR3.03bn (+1.8% QoQ/+6.4% YoY) in line with est.
EDITDA margin came in at 28.7%, in line & PAT at INR1.2bn, below est.
Paid campaigns grew +1.1% QoQ/+4.3% YoY.
Collections reported further slippage of +7.3% QoQ/-1.9% YoY.
Margin decreased due to higher employee cost and advertisement expense
Tweaking FY26E/27E EPS by -5.8%/-3.9%, as cutting growth & profitability expectations in near term due to subdued growth in collections
BOFA on September CPI
Headline inflation at 1.5% YoY, lowest in 100 months
Food & beverage deflation key, vegetable & pulses prices dip further
CPI expected to stay below 4% through 2025
No major GST cut impact seen on CPI
Projecting two 25bps rate cuts in Dec & Feb MPC meetings
October CPI to moderate to 0.5% YoY, series low
UBS on India Gas Utilities
CNG Vehicle addition trend for Sep’25 - Mixed Trend
IGL led with 13,950 CNG vehicle additions (+22% YoY), driven by strong car & LCV demand
MGL saw a 5% YoY decline, weak car & bus additions
GGL reported 37% YoY growth with higher car & 3W registrations
Overall: IGL strong momentum, MGL lags, GGL steady recovery
UBS on Consumer Durables Trends
GST cut boosted LED panel sales
RAC (AC) demand weak due to unseasonal rains
Voltas offers heavy discounts to clear AC stock
Godrej less aggressive; undercuts Voltas by ₹2-3K
Samsung focuses on premium panels & large fridges
LG targets entry-level buyers with 8-10% dealer incentives
Whirlpool passive, Haier pushing rural markets
CLSA on India Oil & Gas Sector
IOC, BPCL, HPCL PAT set for sharp jump on LPG subsidy reimbursement
RIL to see steady QoQ growth; retail & Jio remain strong
ONGC & Oil India profits rise on higher dividend income
Gas demand up 3% QoQ
IGL only player with margin improvement
Macquarie on Eternal
Maintains ‘Underperform’ With Target Price Of ₹200
Expect Rising Competition To Dent Consensus Forecasts
Consensus Overstates Turnaround & Sustainability Of Profits
See Risk Of Reversal In Market Cap
See Limited Margin Of Safety For Shares
